Question: rant about anything
Answer: Today in DBT group the leader was asking us in what kinds of situations do our emotions 'fit the facts' and we were starting with fear. No one was saying anything so I decided to say what came first to my mind and I basically said "when we see a snake we might experience fear" and she was all like smiled and said "I feel like that's more disgust," and I get how she may not wanna write that specifically down bc not everyone is afraid of snakes and there's not always a reason to be afraid of them (though some can be dangerous). But she could have at least accepted my idea as like "if we see something that we think might hurt us or that we have a phobia for, we may experience fear." I mean, that does fit the facts bc the fact is, we are afraid of snakes and so when we see one, it makes sense that we might experience fear. The dismissiveness of my suggestion just made me feel like 'why do I even bother speaking up in group... it gives me anxiety anyway and it just feels like the leaders have smth against whatever I have to say a lot of the time like maybe I just need to stay in the background' and that annoyed me bc I'm trying to work on my anxiety and it's like the world wants to keep giving me reasons on why I should feel uncomfortable... I know this is kinda unreasonable bc not everything we say is gonna be accepted, but it gets really frustrating when it feels like the ratio is really uneven. I think for this particular situation I just felt really invalidated afterward. I'm sure the leader didn't mean to make me feel that way, but she could have approached everything differently than just humiliating me bc I'm scared of snakes. After that, I just kinda tuned out for the rest of group, pretending to listen but really just chilling bc I just felt really frustrated with myself and the group and just life.

Question: Do you like Parry the Platypuss

Would you rather be exempted in an exam that you know you just cheated your way in, or be the presenter in a defense that only you did all the hard work but your teammates gets the credits same as you?
Answer:
Wait, so when you say "exempted in an exam that I cheated in, doesn't that imply that I already did the exam? Bc, I cheated on the exam so I already took it...I'm kinda confused on that...
  
  But either way, I'm tempted to say the former bc I would do almost anything to avoid public speaking, and "presenter" sounds like public speaking. Plus, I don't really have an issue with cheating on exams... I can't really do it bc of morals I guess, but at the same time, I don't really have animosity for people who do bc I think exams are stupid. If the exams were really just for what they are said to be, which is so that the teachers can see where the students are at, then I would be against it all around, but that's not really what exams seem to really be. Exams in my experience typically give students a numeric score that tells the teacher whether they should pass or fail in their class - simply bc of this number. Rarely are we allowed to retake exams, although as humans, we don't all learn things linearly. Sometimes, we start fully realizing how to do something after the exam and then we have the knowledge but that's not reflected in our grade bc we failed the earlier test. So evidently then, the class is not grading us on what we know, it's grading us on our ability to learn complete concepts in small amounts of time, have significant memorization skills, be obedient and get things right on "first times the charm." It's not very fair bc it's not giving an accurate representation of what students have gained in knowledge throughout a class, yet that's the determinate for whether they pass or not. Then teachers have the audacity to say "don't cheat bc the only person you will really be cheating with is yourself." That's not true bc if you cheat and that gives you the right answer, then you have a passing grade and that's what your future is determinate on. So, that went into a very long vent, but basically, my answer is #1. Although, for the record, I don't cheat on tests....

Question: People needs to learn to be patient and not assume you’re ignoring him/her. Like send message and be patient and wait for a reply
Answer: Well, idk your situation, it may be entirely different. But, in general, I don't think it's patience really, I think it's anxiety. I can't speak for everyone, but I know many people feel they lack true connection and friends so when they find someone they think is potential to fill that hole in their life, they wanna chat, bond, etc. When they aren't getting responses, it makes em nervous that you don't like em or they are annoying you or that you don't care as much about the friendship as they do and that creates hard feelings. So, they message more for any kind of validation that they are still your friend and that they did nothing to upset you, you were just busy.

do you believe in destiny? ❣
Answer:
I answered this a few questions ago, so I'll just copy my answer (bc nothing's changed for me in the last 2 mins) 👇🏾:
  
  idk. I thought about this real hard about a month ago or smth, and I just couldn't settle on whether I believe it or not. They say we choose our own destiny, but I don't think we always get to.... Like, George Floyd didn't choose to be murdered. I believe that we all can have dreams that we work towards. But I don't believe that just bc we put a lot of work towards them, we will achieve them. But I guess, destinies don't have to be reached, right? It's just what we feel our place in this world is. But, does everyone believe they have a place in this world? No. Many don't. they don't know their destiny and it depresses them and that becomes sort of a self-fullfiling prophecy after that. it's not their fault tho. some people can't live how they wish they could. some people are statistics of injustice as soon as they are born. some people aren't exposed to things that give them self-actualization when they are younger and so are lost when by the time they are an adult. Some people's lives have shaped them to be constantly anxious, uncomfortable, pessimistic, low-esteemed, feel inferior, sad, full of self-doubt or self-hatred...so their destiny is rigged.
  
  So, sure, I guess I believe in destiny, but only for some. It's part of what makes life so unfair and depressing; some people seem to only be allowed to have fate.
  
  As for me? Idk my destiny. Idk my worth or purpose or importance. I question my life everyday. I'm filled with pessimism and doubt, not bc I want to be, but bc I got "sick" with it. mental illness. or maybe I'm just where I reasonably should be and everyone else is just too happy.

Question: If your best friend doesnot like one of your friend  as she had explosive fight with her and she asks you to stop talking with that friend  .will you quit talking with that friend  or you will keep on talking
Answer:
I would keep talking to them if they are still my friend and I like them and have nothing against them. No friend of mine gets to decide who MY friends are and if they think they do, then maybe they aren't really a friend of mine. But, I think in most situations that I can imagine, if a best friend of mine had an explosive fight with another person, there would be a reason I didn't enjoy that person anymore either and so both of us would cut ties with the person
  
  And also, it's not always about how that person mistreated me, if I feel they really mistreated my friend, then I will cut ties bc no one messes with my friends then gets excused by me. But if both are in the fault or I believe my best friend is the one who made a mistake this time, then I would not leave another friend for no reason except someone else asking/telling me to.
  
  In summary, I am not gonna let someone else decide who my friends are, I'm gonna stick with people who I appreciate who make me feel happy, aren't mean or rude, and who support me back. If the person is no longer that kind of person, then I will cut ties with them. And while I believe that would more likely be the case if a best friend of mine got into a fight with them (bc I would think my best friend and I have more similar beliefs and opinions -- that's park of what would make us best friends), it's not always like that ik, so I would do what I can to support both friends.

Question: What is the worst movie you have ever seen? What made it the worst?

  - Harry Potter and the Halfblood Prince - It just strayed from the original story so much, which wouldn't have been bad, if they hadn't just made it worse.
  
  - Captain America (the first one) - Had no character development. Cap was just the same person throughout the whole movie, just bigger after about half of the movie. He didn't even need to practice or learn how to use his super strength, he just popped out of the experiment knowing how to throw the shield and protect everyone already.
  
  - Iron Man 3 - What the hell was even going on....?
  
  - Inception - It was just sooo boring
  
  - Interstellar & Gravity - I hate movies that take place mainly all in space
